swe.agent.config.codeGeneration.instruct:
A set of instructions that will be added to Copilot requests that generate code.
Instructions can come from: 
- a file in the workspace: `{ "file": "fileName" }`
- text in natural language: `{ "text": "Use underscore for field names." }`

Note: Keep your instructions short and precise. Poor instructions can degrade Copilot's quality and performance.
Use instructions files instead. See https://aka.ms/vscode-ghcp-custom-instructions for more information.
swe.agent.config.codeGeneration.useInstr:
Controls whether code instructions from `.github/copilot-instructions.md` are added to Copilot requests.

Note: Keep your instructions short and precise. Poor instructions can degrade Copilot's quality and performance. [Learn more](https://aka.ms/github-copilot-custom-instructions) about customizing Copilot.
swe.agent.config.codeGeneration.instruct: A text instruction that will be added to Copilot requests that generate code. Optionally, you can specify a language for the instruction.
A path to a file that will be added to Copilot requests that generate code. Optionally, you can specify a language for the instruction.
swe.agent.config.testGeneration.instruct:

swe.agent.config.experimental.testGenera: A text instruction that will be added to Copilot requests that generate tests. Optionally, you can specify a language for the instruction.

swe.agent.config.reviewSelection.enabled: Enables code review on current selection.
swe.agent.config.reviewSelection.instruc:
A set of instructions that will be added to Copilot requests that provide code review for the current selection.
Instructions can come from: 
- a file in the workspace: `{ "file": "fileName" }`
- text in natural language: `{ "text": "Use underscore for field names." }`

Note: Keep your instructions short and precise. Poor instructions can degrade Copilot's effectiveness.
A text instruction that will be added to Copilot requests that provide code review for the current selection. Optionally, you can specify a language for the instruction.
A path to a file that will be added to Copilot requests that provide code review for the current selection. Optionally, you can specify a language for the instruction.
swe.agent.config.commitMessageGeneration:
A set of instructions that will be added to Copilot requests that generate commit messages.
Instructions can come from: 
- a file in the workspace: `{ "file": "fileName" }`
- text in natural language: `{ "text": "Use conventional commit message format." }`

Note: Keep your instructions short and precise. Poor instructions can degrade Copilot's quality and performance.
Text instructions that will be added to Copilot requests that generate commit messages.
A path to a file with instructions that will be added to Copilot requests that generate commit messages.
swe.agent.config.pullRequestDescriptionG:
A set of instructions that will be added to Copilot requests that generate pull request titles and descriptions.
Instructions can come from: 
- a file in the workspace: `{ "file": "fileName" }`
- text in natural language: `{ "text": "Always include a list of key changes." }`

Note: Keep your instructions short and precise. Poor instructions can degrade Copilot's quality and performance.
Text instructions that will be added to Copilot requests that generate pull request titles and descriptions.
A path to a file with instructions that will be added to Copilot requests that generate pull request titles and descriptions.
swe.agent.config.generateTests.codeLens: Show 'Generate tests' code lens for symbols that are not covered by current test coverage information.
swe.agent.config.notebook.followCellExec: Controls whether the currently executing cell is revealed into the viewport upon execution from Copilot.
swe.agent.chat.editor.temporalContext.en: When making inline chat request whether to include recently viewed and edited files with Copilot requests.
swe.agent.chat.edits.temporalContext.ena: When making edits request whether to include recently viewed and edited files with Copilot requests.
swe.agent.config.startDebugging.enabled: Enables the `/startDebugging` intent in panel chat. Generates or finds launch config to match the query (if any), project structure, and more.
swe.agent.config.agent.thinkingTool: Enables the thinking tool that allows Copilot to think deeply about your request before generating a response in agent mode.
swe.agent.config.setupTests.enabled: Enables the `/setupTests` intent and prompting in `/tests` generation.
swe.agent.config.byok.ollamaEndpoint: The endpoint to use for the Ollama when accessed via bring your own key. Defaults to localhost.
swe.agent.config.virtualTools.threshold:
This setting defines the tool count over which virtual tools should be used. Virtual tools group similar sets of tools together and they allow the model to activate them on-demand. Certain tool groups will optimistically be pre-activated. We are actively developing this feature and you experience degraded tool calling once the threshold is hit.

May be set to `0` to disable virtual tools.
swe.agent.config.retryAfterFilteredRespo: Enables retrying after a filtered response. If enabled, Copilot Chat will retry the request after a content filter blocks the response.
swe.agent.config.alternateGptPrompt.enab: Enables an experimental alternate prompt for GPT models instead of the default prompt.
swe.agent.config.gpt5AlternatePrompt: Specifies an experimental alternate prompt to use for GPT-5 models. When set, this custom prompt will be used instead of the default system prompt for GPT-5.

swe.agent.walkthrough.title: SWE Agent
swe.agent.walkthrough.description: Your AI pair programmer to write code faster and smarter
swe.agent.walkthrough.signIn.title: Sign in with GitHub
swe.agent.walkthrough.signIn.description:
To get started with Copilot, sign in with your GitHub account.
Make sure you're using the correct GitHub account. You can also sign in later using the account menu.

[Sign In](command:swe.agent.signIn)
swe.agent.walkthrough.signIn.media.altTe: Sign in to GitHub via this walkthrough or VS Code's account menu
swe.agent.walkthrough.setup.signIn.title: Sign in to use Copilot for free
swe.agent.walkthrough.setup.signIn.descr:
You can use Copilot to generate code across multiple files, fix errors, ask questions about your code and much more using natural language.
 We now offer [Copilot for free](https://github.com/features/copilot/plans) with your GitHub account.

[Use Copilot for Free](command:workbench.action.chat.triggerSetupForceSignIn)

swe.agent.walkthrough.firstSuggest.title: AI-suggested code completions
swe.agent.walkthrough.firstSuggest.descr: As you type in the editor, Copilot suggests code to help you complete what you started.
swe.agent.walkthrough.firstSuggest.media: The video shows different Copilot completions, where Copilot suggests code to help the user complete their code
swe.agent.walkthrough.panelChat.title: Chat about your code
swe.agent.walkthrough.panelChat.descript:
Ask Copilot programming questions or get help with your code using **@workspace**.
 Type **@** to see all available chat participants that you can chat with directly, each with their own expertise.
[Chat with Copilot](command:workbench.action.chat.open?%7B%22mode%22%3A%22ask%22%7D)
swe.agent.walkthrough.panelChat.media.al: The user invokes @workspace in the Copilot Chat panel in the secondary sidebar to understand the code base. Copilot retrieves the relevant information and provides a response with links to the files
swe.agent.walkthrough.inlineChatNotMac.t: Use natural language in your files
swe.agent.walkthrough.inlineChatNotMac.d:
Sometimes, it's easier to describe the code you want to write directly within a file.
Place your cursor or make a selection and use **``Ctrl+I``** to open **Inline Chat**.
swe.agent.walkthrough.inlineChatNotMac.m: Inline Chat view in the editor. The video shows the user invoking the inline chat widget and asking Copilot to make a change in the file using natural language. Copilot then makes the requested change
swe.agent.walkthrough.inlineChatMac.titl: Use natural language in your files
swe.agent.walkthrough.inlineChatMac.desc:
Sometimes, it's easier to describe the code you want to write directly within a file.
Place your cursor or make a selection and use **``Cmd+I``** to open **Inline Chat**.
swe.agent.walkthrough.inlineChatMac.medi: The video shows the user invoking the inline chat widget and asking Copilot to make a change in the file using natural language. Copilot then makes the requested change
swe.agent.walkthrough.edits.title: Make changes using natural language
swe.agent.walkthrough.edits.description:
Use **Copilot Edits** to select files you want to work with and describe changes you want to make. Copilot applies them directly to your files.
[Edit with Copilot](command:workbench.action.chat.open?%7B%22mode%22%3A%22edit%22%7D)
swe.agent.walkthrough.edits.media.altTex: The video shows the user dragging and dropping files into the Copilot Edits input box located in the secondary sidebar. Copilot then updates the file according to the user’s request
swe.agent.walkthrough.sparkle.title: Look out for smart actions
swe.agent.walkthrough.sparkle.descriptio:
Copilot enhances your coding experience with AI-powered smart actions throughout the VS Code interface.
Look for $(sparkle) icons, such as in the [Source Control view](command:workbench.view.scm), where Copilot generates commit messages and PR descriptions based on code changes.

[Discover Tips and Tricks](https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/copilot/copilot-vscode-features)
swe.agent.walkthrough.sparkle.media.altT: The video shows the sparkle icon in the source control input box being clicked, triggering GitHub Copilot to generate a commit message automatically
